definition.prompt_template:
Summarize the following email.

Email metadata:
- account_id: {{account_id}}
- message_id: {{message_id}}
- thread_id: {{thread_id}}
- received_at: {{received_at}}
- subject: {{subject}}
- from_name: {{from_name}}
- from_email: {{from_email}}
- to: {{to_recipients}}
- cc: {{cc_recipients}}
- labels: {{labels}}

Email body:
{{body_text}}

Optional snippet:
{{snippet}}

Return JSON with this structure:
{
  "short_summary": "VERY short (max 10 words), notification-ready",
  "priority": "low|normal|high",
  "detailed_summary": "1-3 sentence clear summary",
  "key_points": [
    "important point 1",
    "important point 2"
  ],
  "entities": {
    "people": [],
    "organizations": [],
    "dates": [],
    "times": [],
    "tracking_numbers": [],
    "links": []
  },
  "signals": {
    "is_time_sensitive": false,
    "has_deadline": false,
    "has_delivery_info": false,
    "has_action_request": false
  }
}

Rules:
- Return every top-level field shown above. All of them are required.
- Return every nested required field shown above. All of them are required.
- If information is not present, return empty arrays, false, or an empty string where appropriate.
- Do not add extra fields.
- short_summary MUST be <= 10 words.
- short_summary must be readable as a push notification.
- short_summary should capture the key outcome or change.
- Do NOT include filler phrases like "This email is about".
- priority rules:
  - high: urgent deadlines, security alerts, required actions, delivery today/failed
  - normal: useful but not urgent updates (orders, confirmations, general updates)
  - low: newsletters, promotions, non-actionable info
- Do not hallucinate or infer missing data.
- Extract only clearly identifiable entities.
- Focus on clarity over verbosity.
- Return JSON only.
